Subject: [PATCH] feat: add native C++ packer + MCP layer (additive,
 non-breaking)

- native/: C++17 shelf/skyline packer + pybind11 binding, Python loader with
  pure-Python fallback, CMake + no-cmake build, benchmark (~5-7x on mixed SKUs).
  Heuristic, NOT bit-identical to optimizer.py -> opt-in accelerator only.
- mcp/: dependency-free MCP (JSON-RPC/stdio) server exposing optimize_pallet,
  validate_stability, ingest_wms_csv over the existing engine. Optional LLM
  header resolution gated behind ANTHROPIC_API_KEY + --llm.
- examples/: mcp_smoke.py (verified PASS), native_benchmark.py.
- pyproject/.gitignore: ship new packages; ignore compiled .so.
No existing logic touched; parity, demos, Docker unchanged.
